HEADWORD: Misdirect
<hw>Mis`di*rect"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To give a
wrong direction to; <as>as, to <ex>misdirect</ex> a passenger, or a
letter; to <ex>misdirect</ex> one's energies.</as></def>
<rj><au>Shenstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

